{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":748,"text":"Sydney. I had been waiting my whole life to get to Sydney."},{"time":4427,"text":"I got to the airport, to the hotel, checked in,"},{"time":7474,"text":"and, sitting there in the lobby, was a brochure"},{"time":10253,"text":"for the Sydney Festival. I thumbed through it,"},{"time":12875,"text":"and I came across a show called \"Minto: Live.\""},{"time":16016,"text":"The description read: \"The suburban streets of Minto"},{"time":19648,"text":"become the stage for performances"},{"time":22189,"text":"created by international artists"},{"time":24395,"text":"in collaboration with the people of Minto.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":27195,"text":"What was this place called Minto?"},{"time":29910,"text":"Sydney, as I would learn, is a city of suburbs,"},{"time":32271,"text":"and Minto lies southwest, about an hour away."},{"time":35944,"text":"I have to say, it wasn't exactly what I had in mind"},{"time":39303,"text":"for my first day down under."},{"time":40900,"text":"I mean, I'd thought about the Harbour Bridge or Bondi Beach,"},{"time":43839,"text":"but Minto? But still, I'm a producer,"},{"time":46795,"text":"and the lure of a site-specific theater project"},{"time":49967,"text":"was more than I could resist. (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":52236,"text":"So, off I went into Friday afternoon traffic,"},{"time":54720,"text":"and I'll never forget what I saw when I got there."},{"time":57125,"text":"For the performance, the audience walked"},{"time":59779,"text":"around the neighborhood from house to house,"},{"time":62569,"text":"and the residents, who were the performers,"},{"time":65449,"text":"they came out of their houses, and they performed"},{"time":67560,"text":"these autobiographical dances on their lawns,"},{"time":71399,"text":"on their driveways. (Laughter)"},{"time":73747,"text":"The show is a collaboration with a U.K.-based"},{"time":76715,"text":"performance company called Lone Twin."},{"time":79374,"text":"Lone Twin had come to Minto and worked"},{"time":81270,"text":"with the residents, and they had created these dances."}]},{"cues":[{"time":84394,"text":"This Australian-Indian girl, she came out and started"},{"time":88232,"text":"to dance on her front lawn,"},{"time":90253,"text":"and her father peered out the window to see"},{"time":93191,"text":"what all the noise and commotion was about,"},{"time":95698,"text":"and he soon joined her."},{"time":97906,"text":"And he was followed by her little sister."},{"time":101033,"text":"And soon they were all dancing this joyous,"},{"time":104091,"text":"exuberant dance right there on their lawn. (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":108266,"text":"And as I walked through the neighborhood,"},{"time":110458,"text":"I was amazed and I was moved by the incredible"},{"time":114679,"text":"sense of ownership this community clearly felt"},{"time":117116,"text":"about this event."},{"time":119686,"text":"\"Minto: Live\" brought Sydneysiders into dialogue"},{"time":122645,"text":"with international artists, and really celebrated"},{"time":125975,"text":"the diversity of Sydney on its own terms."}]},{"cues":[{"time":129463,"text":"The Sydney Festival which produced \"Minto: Live\" I think"},{"time":133176,"text":"represents a new kind of 21st-century arts festival."},{"time":136951,"text":"These festivals are radically open."},{"time":140466,"text":"They can transform cities and communities."}]},{"cues":[{"time":144178,"text":"To understand this, I think it kind of makes sense"},{"time":146858,"text":"to look where we've come from."},{"time":149184,"text":"Modern arts festivals were born"},{"time":151207,"text":"in the rubble of World War II."},{"time":152705,"text":"Civic leaders created these annual events"},{"time":155307,"text":"to celebrate culture as the highest"},{"time":158416,"text":"expression of the human spirit."},{"time":161021,"text":"In 1947, the Edinburgh Festival was born"},{"time":164104,"text":"and Avignon was born and hundreds of others"},{"time":166761,"text":"would follow in their wake."},{"time":168662,"text":"The work they did was very, very high art,"},{"time":171914,"text":"and stars came along like Laurie Anderson"},{"time":174518,"text":"and Merce Cunningham and Robert Lepage"},{"time":176793,"text":"who made work for this circuit,"},{"time":178213,"text":"and you had these seminal shows like \"The Mahabharata\""},{"time":180984,"text":"and the monumental \"Einstein on the Beach.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":183969,"text":"But as the decades passed,"},{"time":186464,"text":"these festivals, they really became the establishment,"},{"time":189665,"text":"and as the culture and capital accelerated,"},{"time":193058,"text":"the Internet brought us all together,"},{"time":195059,"text":"high and low kind of disappeared,"},{"time":197991,"text":"a new kind of festival emerged."}]},{"cues":[{"time":199613,"text":"The old festivals, they continued to thrive, but"},{"time":202752,"text":"from Brighton to Rio to Perth, something new was emerging,"},{"time":207100,"text":"and these festivals were really different."},{"time":210044,"text":"They're open, these festivals, because, like in Minto,"},{"time":212939,"text":"they understand that the dialogue"},{"time":215155,"text":"between the local and the global is essential."},{"time":218873,"text":"They're open because they ask the audience to be a player,"},{"time":223376,"text":"a protagonist, a partner, rather than a passive spectator,"},{"time":227786,"text":"and they're open because they know that imagination"},{"time":231365,"text":"cannot be contained in buildings,"},{"time":233524,"text":"and so much of the work they do"},{"time":235377,"text":"is site-specific or outdoor work."}]},{"cues":[{"time":238677,"text":"So, the new festival, it asks the audience to play"},{"time":242065,"text":"an essential role in shaping the performance."},{"time":245183,"text":"Companies like De La Guarda, which I produce, and Punchdrunk"},{"time":250279,"text":"create these completely immersive experiences"},{"time":253093,"text":"that put the audience at the center of the action,"},{"time":256288,"text":"but the German performance company Rimini Protokoll"},{"time":259390,"text":"takes this all to a whole new level."},{"time":262677,"text":"In a series of shows that includes \"100 Percent Vancouver,\""},{"time":266459,"text":"\"100 Percent Berlin,\" Rimini Protokoll makes shows"},{"time":270456,"text":"that actually reflect society."},{"time":273289,"text":"Rimini Protokoll chooses 100 people that represent that city"},{"time":277826,"text":"at that moment in terms of race and gender and class,"},{"time":281237,"text":"through a careful process that begins three months before,"},{"time":284511,"text":"and then those 100 people share stories about"},{"time":287738,"text":"themselves and their lives, and the whole thing"},{"time":290274,"text":"becomes a snapshot of that city at that moment."},{"time":294896,"text":"LIFT has always been a pioneer in the use of venues."},{"time":298331,"text":"They understand that theater and performance"},{"time":300742,"text":"can happen anywhere."},{"time":302060,"text":"You can do a show in a schoolroom,"},{"time":305269,"text":"in an airport, — (Laughter) —"},{"time":307654,"text":"in a department store window."}]},{"cues":[{"time":310139,"text":"Artists are explorers. Who better to show us the city anew?"},{"time":314561,"text":"Artists can take us to a far-flung part of the city"},{"time":317908,"text":"that we haven't explored, or they can take us into"},{"time":319936,"text":"that building that we pass every day but we never went into."}]},{"cues":[{"time":324361,"text":"An artist, I think, can really show us people"},{"time":328524,"text":"that we might overlook in our lives."},{"time":331663,"text":"Back to Back is an Australian company of people"},{"time":335058,"text":"with intellectual disabilities. I saw their amazing show"},{"time":339644,"text":"in New York at the Staten Island Ferry Terminal"},{"time":342813,"text":"at rush hour."},{"time":344223,"text":"We, the audience, were given headsets and seated"},{"time":346943,"text":"on one side of the terminal."},{"time":349727,"text":"The actors were right there in front of us,"},{"time":351719,"text":"right there among the commuters,"},{"time":354129,"text":"and we could hear them,"},{"time":355689,"text":"but we might not have otherwise seen them."},{"time":358784,"text":"So Back to Back takes site-specific theater and uses it"},{"time":363302,"text":"to gently remind us about who and what we choose"},{"time":366576,"text":"to edit out of our daily lives."}]},{"cues":[{"time":369467,"text":"So, the dialogue with the local and the global,"},{"time":372579,"text":"the audience as participant and player and protagonist,"},{"time":376489,"text":"the innovative use of site, all of these things"},{"time":379617,"text":"come to play in the amazing work"},{"time":382466,"text":"of the fantastic French company Royal de Luxe."},{"time":386523,"text":"Royal de Luxe's giant puppets come into a city"},{"time":390263,"text":"and they live there for a few days."}]},{"cues":[{"time":393016,"text":"For \"The Sultan's Elephant,\" Royal de Luxe"},{"time":396590,"text":"came to central London and brought it to a standstill"},{"time":399613,"text":"with their story of a giant little girl and her friend,"},{"time":404002,"text":"a time-traveling elephant."},{"time":406514,"text":"For a few days, they transformed a massive city"},{"time":411183,"text":"into a community where endless possibility reigned."},{"time":416086,"text":"The Guardian wrote, \"If art is about transformation,"},{"time":419677,"text":"then there can be no more transformative experience."},{"time":423667,"text":"What 'The Sultan's Elephant' represents is no less"},{"time":427567,"text":"than an artistic occupation of the city"},{"time":430413,"text":"and a reclamation of the streets for the people.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":435290,"text":"We can talk about the economic impacts of these festivals"},{"time":438750,"text":"on their cities, but I'm much [more] interested in many more things,"},{"time":443056,"text":"like how a festival helps a city to express itself,"},{"time":446821,"text":"how it lets it come into its own."},{"time":450092,"text":"Festivals promote diversity,"},{"time":452217,"text":"they bring neighbors into dialogue,"},{"time":454203,"text":"they increase creativity,"},{"time":456648,"text":"they offer opportunities for civic pride,"},{"time":459820,"text":"they improve our general psychological well-being."},{"time":463479,"text":"In short, they make cities better places to live."}]},{"cues":[{"time":467687,"text":"Case in point:"},{"time":468665,"text":"When \"The Sultan's Elephant\" came to London"},{"time":472009,"text":"just nine months after 7/7, a Londoner wrote,"},{"time":476365,"text":"\"For the first time since the London bombings,"},{"time":479998,"text":"my daughter called up with that sparkle back in her voice."},{"time":483608,"text":"She had gathered with others"},{"time":485350,"text":"to watch 'The Sultan's Elephant,' and, you know,"},{"time":488538,"text":"it just made all the difference.\""},{"time":491221,"text":"Lyn Gardner in The Guardian has written"},{"time":493371,"text":"that a great festival can show us a map of the world,"},{"time":497834,"text":"a map of the city and a map of ourselves,"},{"time":501882,"text":"but there is no one fixed festival model."},{"time":505088,"text":"I think what's so brilliant about the festivals,"},{"time":507924,"text":"the new festivals, is that they are really fully capturing"},{"time":512990,"text":"the complexity and the excitement"},{"time":516178,"text":"of the way we all live today."},{"time":518203,"text":"Thank you very much. (Applause)"}]}]}